def plotImages(images_arr):
	fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,5,figsize=(50,50))
	axes = axes.flatten()
	for img,ax in zip(images_arr,axes):
		ax.imshow(img)
		ax.axis('off')
	plt.tight_layout()
	plt.show()

def plot_confusion_matrix(cm,classes,normalize=False,title='Confusion Matrix',cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
    plt.imshow(cm,interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(classes))
    plt.xticks(tick_marks,classes,rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks,classes)
    if normalize:
        cm = cm.astype('float')/cm.sum(axis=1)[:,np.newaxis]
    else:
        pass
    print(cm)
    thresh = cm.max()/2
    for i, j in itertools.product(range(cm.shape[0]),range(cm.shape[1])):
        plt.text(j,i,cm[i,j],horizontalalignment="center",		color="white" if cm[i,j]>thresh else "black")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True Label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted Label')

def load_image(filename):
    # load the image
    imgage_classification = load_img(filename, target_size=(500, 500))
    # convert to array
    imgage_classification = img_to_array(imgage_classification)
    # reshape into a single sample with 3 channels
    imgage_classification = imgage_classification.reshape(1, 500, 500, 3)
    # prepare pixel data
    imgage_classification = imgage_classification.astype('float32')
    imgage_classification = imgage_classification / 255.0
    
#     from skimage.io import imread
#     import cv2
#     import skimage
    # image = imread('C:\\Users\\arkh\\Keras_Classfication_FYP\\DataSet\\train\\NORMAL\\01.jpeg')
    image_segmentation = imread(image_dir)
    IMG_SIZE = (image_segmentation.shape[0],image_segmentation.shape[1])
    image_segmentation = cv2.resize(image_segmentation,dsize=IMG_SIZE,interpolation=cv2.INTER_CUBIC)
    if image_segmentation.ndim != 3:
        image_segmentation = skimage.color.gray2rgb(image_segmentation)
    if image_segmentation.shape[-1] == 4:
        image_segmentation = image_segmentation[..., :3]
    return imgage_classification,image_segmentation
